[BT] LLM decision: GeneratePRContent -> {"prTitle":"feat(frontend): add weather UI with geolocation and forecast ranges","prBody":"## Summary\nThis PR implements a minimal weather interface in the Vite + React + TypeScript frontend so users can fetch forecasts either by typing a location or by using browser geolocation. It adds controls for single-day, 3-day, and full-week forecast retrieval and wires them to backend endpoints with lightweight state handling via vanilla React + `fetch`. The update also hardens UX behavior with loading/error/result handling and request race protection so only the latest response is rendered, improving reliability on desktop and mobile.\n\n## Changes Made\n- `src/App.tsx`: Built the main weather UI flow, including manual location input, geolocation trigger, forecast range controls (day/3-day/week), fetch actions, and responsive-friendly interaction states.\n- `src/forecastApi.ts`: Added/updated frontend API helpers that call backend forecast endpoints for location and coordinate-based requests across supported ranges.\n- `src/style.css`: Added minimal styling for layout, controls, and readable results/error/loading states with functional behavior across desktop and mobile viewports.\n- `src/main.tsx`: Ensured React app bootstrap mounts the updated weather UI.\n- `index.html`: Kept/updated Vite entry shell metadata and mount point used by the frontend.\n- `tests/app-ui.test.tsx`: Added UI-focused tests covering manual entry, geolocation path, forecast range selection, request handling, and visible UX states.\n- `tests/forecast-api.test.ts`: Added API utility tests validating request construction/behavior for forecast fetch calls.\n- `package.json` / `package-lock.json`: Updated scripts/dependencies to support frontend test execution in the project’s Node-based test workflow.\n- `tsconfig.json`, `src/App.ts`, `src/main.ts`: Updated compatibility/typing/export surface to align with the Vite TypeScript app structure and test/build setup.\n- `logs_llm/mcp-server-2026-03-05.log`: Runtime log file changed in workspace; not part of functional frontend behavior.\n\n## Testing\n- `npm test`: **14 passed, 0 failed** (QA-verified).\n- Engineer auto-verification also reports:\n  - Build passed (`tsc && vite build`)\n  - Type checks passed\n  - Runtime/smoke checks passed\n  - Frontend test command passed (`npm run test:frontend`, 14/14)\n- QA final status: **Approved**, confirming requirements for manual location, auto geolocation, day/3-day/week forecast views, backend wiring, and desktop/mobile functionality.\n\n## Context\n- Task: **Build minimal Vite frontend weather UI with manual and auto location options**.\n- Target branch: `main`.\n- No breaking changes were reported.\n- Release automation noted PR creation/push failure only because the repo has no configured `origin` remote (local-only environment), not due to code quality issues.\n- Confidence: **0.99**."}
